# Custom Fields Implementation Plan – Resumes Tab

This section extends the plan to cover the **Resumes** tab (candidate profiles stored in `resumesDB`).

## Key Research Findings

| Finding | Detail |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Collection** | `MRv5.resumesDB` |
| **Data path** | `customData.<companyID>.<fieldID>.{label, format, value}` — **identical to campaigns** |
| **Layout source** | [.trash/Schema_Data/ProfileLayouts/layouts.txt](file:///c:/Users/pratik/MRv5-TSX/MapRecruit.ai-TypeScript-/.trash/Schema_Data/ProfileLayouts/layouts.txt) (NOT [LayoutsCustomData.json](file:///c:/Users/pratik/MRv5-TSX/MapRecruit.ai-TypeScript-/.trash/SchemaData/LayoutsCustomData.json)) |
| **Schema model** | [Candidate.js](file:///c:/Users/pratik/MRv5-TSX/MapRecruit.ai-TypeScript-/backend/models/Candidate.js) uses `strict: false` — no schema changes needed |
| **Live evidence** | Doc `690983bcb7f941d7bdaf0a27` has `customData.6112806bc9147f673d28c6eb.61c955e903926f6b5e9a2822 = {label:"Primary BU",format:"Text",value:"TRC Talent Solutions - TRC Talent Solutions"}` |

